The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 26: Leading economic think-tank NCAER has advocated a slew of policy reforms, including a flexible labour regime, to boost exports. ?Merchandise exports have started facing infrastructural bottlenecks as well as policy impediments arising from continued slips on reforming labour and exit laws,? the National Council of Applied Economic Research said in its monthly report. ?A conducive environment should be provided to bring in new investment both in high-tech as well as labour-intensive sectors of production,? it added.

 New Delhi, April 26: The Supreme Court today fixed May 5 as the date for hearing a petition filed by Anil Ambani- owned Reliance Airport Developers, which has challenged the Delhi High Court verdict upholding the government?s decision to allot Delhi and Mumbai airports? modernisation work to the GMR and GVK-led consortia.

 New Delhi, April 26: Chartered accountants today protested against the imposition of service tax on taxation and legal services, saying it put them at a disadvantage against others offering similar services.

 Mumbai, April 26: IPCL today said on May 4 it would consider the interim dividend payout to shareholders for 2005-06.

 Mumbai, April 26: Mahindra amp; Mahindra Ltd today said it has allotted 18.62 lakh shares upon conversion of foreign currency convertible bonds.




